text: - Hi everyone, I'm Ryan Myrehn,

and I'm excited to bring you
the next evolution in racing.

The world's first global
autonomous racing league,
AWS DeepRacer.
Since launch, over 140,000 developers

from more than 150
countries have participated.

And this year, the DeepRacer
league is more accessible
than ever before.

With the all new Student
League, presented by Intel,

high school and college
students worldwide can compete
for scholarships, prizes, and glory.

Students can get rolling
with just a few clicks,
no credit card required.

All new AWS DeepRacer arcades
will let you skip the coding,

grab the wheel, and race
head to head against AI.
Compete from anywhere in the world
in monthly virtual circuit races.
And the Summit Circuit is back,

in person on physical
tracks across the globe,

with more chances to qualify
for one of 50 coveted spots
in the championships at re:Invent.
Discover how you can accelerate
your machine learning journey
at deepracerleague.com.
